- "Big 10 conference" is a collegiate athletic conference;
- "passing yards" refers to the total distance covered by the football when thrown and caught during a game;
- "average passing yards per game" is calculated by dividing the total passing yards by the number of games played.

- "Experienced coaches" refers to coaches with more than 10 years of experience;
- "Winning percentage over 70%" means a winning percentage greater than 0.7;
- "Score more points than the average team" means the team's total points for is greater than the average total points for across all teams.

sql:
SELECT team_name
FROM teams
ORDER BY stadium_capacity DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "Champion" refers to the team with the highest total points for the season;
- "Standing tall" implies the team is ranked first;
- "Total points for the season" is the sum of points scored by the team across all games.

- "Top-performing team" refers to the team with the highest total score across all games;
- "Performance metrics" include total score, total opponent score, and average attendance;
- "Most experienced coach" is the coach with the highest number of years of experience for that team;
- "Rivalry information" includes the name of any rivalry the team is involved in, with 'No Rivalry' if none exists.

- Teams with more than 1000 total engagements and a winning percentage greater than 0.7 are categorized as 'High' engagement;
- Teams with fewer than 500 total engagements and a winning percentage less than 0.4 are categorized as 'Low' engagement;
- All other teams are categorized as 'Medium' engagement.

- "stand tall as the champions" refers to teams with the highest number of wins;
- "records of triumph, power, and glory" include total wins, total points scored, and average points scored;
- "ranking in the league" is determined by the number of total wins.
